The good endevours of the Lord, you may read in theſe words,Iſa. 5.3, 4. O Inhabitants of Jeruſalem and men of Judah, judge I pray you between me and
my Vineyard;
Serm. 4. what could have been done more to my Vineyard that I have not done to it? The good Lord, though indeed our God and our King, He puts himſelf upon his people, he would have the Vineyard, to ſay whether he had not done his part! And indeed, for a thriving Vineyard, or for an happy people, what had he not provided? What had not he condeſcended to?
